headline: This Homebuilder Stock Just Got A Rating Upgrade, But It's A Fixer-Upper. Here's Why.
summary: On Thursday, homebuilder PulteGroup got a notable upgrade to its Relative Strength (RS) Rating, from 66 to 80.  The upgraded RS Rating shows that Pulte outpaced 80% of all stocks for price performance over the last 52 weeks.  It's notable because market research shows that the best stocks often have an RS Rating north of 80 as they begin their biggest climbs.
